<HEADLINE> Thai Military Confirms Death of Pol Pot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 16 (Xinhua) -- The Thai military on Thursday
confirmed the death of Pol Pot, former leader of the Khmer Rouge.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Thai TV Channel Nine showed the corpse of Pol Pot
wearing a grey shirt. He was lying on a bed in a cottage in
Cambodia near the border with Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Red flowers were put on the two sides of his head, and on the
right side of his corpse was a fan which was frequently used by
Pol Pot when he was alive. His slippers were in front of the bed.
</P>
<P>
A Thai military officer, Viwat Sadala, said in Thailand's
northeastern Surin province bordering Cambodia that he saw the
corpse of Pol Pot and filmed it.
</P>
<P>
Supreme Commander of Thailand's armed forces, General Mongkol
Ampornpisith, said earlier that he would send troops on the
Thai-Cambodia border to confirm the death of Pol Pot.
</P>
<P>
Pol Pot reportedly died of a heart attack late Wednesday night
in the Cambodian territory.
</P>
<P>
The TV report said the Khmer Rouge would cremate Pol Pot's
corpse in two or three days. The cremation was originally planned
for later on Thursday night.  
</P>
